HEADWORD: Tinner
<hw>Tin"ner</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
works in a tin mine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who makes, or works in, tinware; a
tinman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinnient</ent>⟦br⟧
